=>   Given an integer x, return true if x is a palindrome, and false otherwise.

     Example 1:
          Input: x = 121
          Output: true
          Explanation: 121 reads as 121 from left to right and from right to left.

     Constraints:
          -2^31 <= x <= 2^31 - 1


=> MY CODE :
    public boolean isPalindrome(int x) {
        if(x < 0) return false;

        int revX = 0;
        int tempX = x;

        while(tempX != 0){
            int lastDigit = tempX % 10;
            revX = (revX * 10) + lastDigit;
            tempX = tempX / 10;
        }

        return x == revX;
    }



=> OPTIMIZED : Here, we only reverse half and check it with other half to avoid integer overflow and faster execution
    public boolean isPalindrome(int x) {
        if (x < 0 || (x % 10 == 0 && x != 0)) {
            return false;
        }

        int rev = 0;

        while(x > rev){
            rev = (rev * 10) + (x % 10);
            x =  x / 10;
        }
        
        return x == rev || x == rev / 10;
    }
  
